    <custom_item>
      system        : "Linux"
      type          : CMD_EXEC
      description   : "GEN000340 - UIDs reserved for system accounts must not be assigned to non-system accounts."
      info          : "Reserved UIDs are typically used by system software packages.  If non-system accounts have UIDs in this range, they may conflict with system software, possibly leading to the user having permissions to modify system files."
      solution      : "Change the UID numbers for non-system accounts with reserved UIDs (those less or equal to 499)."
